<dl id="n08131b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08131b">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08131b"> 131(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Chas Clagget (Ir) invented / piston valve horns</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>German Military Music</b> <font color="green">[by W. H. Grattan Flood]</font>: The <mark>invention of the valve-horn</mark> was a most valuable asset to the military band &hellip; sober history records that the <mark>piston valves</mark> were certainly <mark>due to an Irishman, Charles Clagget</mark>, in 1787, full twenty-seven years before the German patent. <small> <a name="IS2feb24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IS2feb24"><cite title="source">Irish Statesman</cite></a> (2 February 1924) 658b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
